<dl id="n54125f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n54" href="#n54125f">N54 (VI.B.45)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n54all.htm#n54125f"> 125(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> comb &amp; scissors</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The hunting of the Boar (the <i>porcus Troit</i>) is one of the main features of the story; <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> Many strange men and beasts and implements were required for the chase and despatch of Twrch Trwyth, and for the capture of &ldquo;the <mark>comb and scissors</mark>&rdquo; between his ears, which Yspaddaden wanted for the proper trimming of his unruly hair. <small> W. Lewis Jones, <a name="WJKA4" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#WJKA4"><cite title="source">King Arthur in History and Legend</cite></a> (1914) 48</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
